      "message": "[Major] Line 2110: 🟡 Suggestions: `identityRetryState_` is mutated from `identityAnnouncedCb` and also from the Asio timer callback without any visible strand/mutex guarantee. If the DHT callback and `Manager::ioContext()` handler can run on different threads, this introduces a data race on `attempt`, `exhausted`, and the shared pointer itself. Route all retry-state reads/writes through the same io_context/strand or protect them with the account mutex used for related state.",
