      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 2115: 🔴 Critical Issues: `identityRetryState_` is only reset after a successful identity announcement. If retries are exhausted during a transient offline/GSM standby period, `state.exhausted` remains true and later failures in the same account lifetime will return immediately without scheduling any retry, so presence/device sync can remain permanently broken until account recreation. Reset the retry state when a new registration/connectivity cycle starts, or reset exhausted state when connectivity is restored before trying to re-announce. Suggested fix example:\n```suggestion\nif (identityRetryState_) {\n    identityRetryState_-\u003etimer.cancel();\n    identityRetryState_.reset();\n}\n```\nPlace this at the beginning of the account/DHT restart path that represents a fresh registration cycle, before identity announcement can fail again.",
      "revId": "cac54065c7a242a75719e2f4dd415fac87542238",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
